v:4 c:$ m:T02-metronome-sync role:dev x:webaudio/netcode
gate: LOCKED

task: Produce a network-synced metronome click locked to the shared transport clock

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/glicol-engine.ts
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/network-bridge.ts
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/composables/useJamSession.ts

depends: [T01-transport-controls]

context: |
  transport.currentBeat gives a running beat position from bpm + startTime.
  Peers already clock-sync via NTP-style ping/pong (peerOffsets → averageOffset),
  and notes schedule against transport.now. To make the metronome SHARED, all
  peers must agree on (a) bpm and (b) the beat-0 origin (startTime).

  Free message code: use 0x07 = MSG_TRANSPORT for bpm + startTime broadcast.

steps (sync):
  1. network-bridge: add MSG_TRANSPORT (0x07). Encode bpm (uint16) + transport
     startTime origin so a joining peer can align beat phase. On receipt, apply
     to local transport (setBpm + adjust startTime via the existing clock offset)
     and notify via a new onTransportUpdate handler.
  2. On a peer JOIN, an already-running peer should send current transport state
     (reuse the existing "reply with join" pattern timing).
  3. useJamSession.setBpm should also broadcast MSG_TRANSPORT so tempo changes
     propagate (mirror how sendScaleUpdate works).

steps (click):
  4. glicol-engine: add a metronome voice. On each beat boundary (derive from
     transport.currentBeat crossing an integer in the scheduler tick from S03/
     existing scheduler), play a short click — acc(downbeat) vs normal (other
     beats). Keep it a tiny Glicol chain; respect global mute.
  5. Gate the click on metronomeOn (from T01). Metronome is LOCAL audio only
     (each peer hears their own click in sync — do NOT send click as a note).

done:
  - Metronome clicks on the beat at the set BPM
  - Two peers (two tabs / broadcast mode) hear clicks IN PHASE with each other
  - Changing BPM on one peer updates the other's tempo
  - Downbeat is audibly distinct from other beats
  - Respects global mute; off by default
  - tsc --noEmit passes
